6968
04:06:27,899 --> 04:06:28,559
So that was it?

6969
04:06:28,680 --> 04:06:31,500
Didn't you ever see Stone Mover again?

6970
04:06:31,559 --> 04:06:34,500
No, but of course that wasn't it.

6971
04:06:34,620 --> 04:06:37,319
Thorn said, turning to walk on again.

6972
04:06:37,379 --> 04:06:39,420
I looked for him everywhere.

6973
04:06:39,479 --> 04:06:41,879
I went through the tunnel, but it led to

6974
04:06:41,879 --> 04:06:43,920
the rainforest. isn't that odd?

6975
04:06:43,979 --> 04:06:46,079
I thought it would lead to their hidden

6976
04:06:46,079 --> 04:06:48,899
kingdom, but no, I searched the whole

6977
04:06:48,899 --> 04:06:51,000
place, but there were no night wings

6978
04:06:51,000 --> 04:06:51,299
there.

6979
04:06:51,360 --> 04:06:54,420
Only some very sweet, rather bewildered

6980
04:06:54,420 --> 04:06:55,139
rain wings.

6981
04:06:55,200 --> 04:06:56,639
Very confusing.

6982
04:06:56,700 --> 04:06:58,739
I never understood how that would save

6983
04:06:58,739 --> 04:06:59,280
his tribe.

6984
04:06:59,340 --> 04:07:02,700
I'll explain it to you later, Sonny

6985
04:07:02,700 --> 04:07:02,940
said.

6986
04:07:03,000 --> 04:07:04,260
Did he know about me?

6987
04:07:04,319 --> 04:07:05,639
No.

6988
04:07:05,700 --> 04:07:06,840
Thorn said.

6989
04:07:06,899 --> 04:07:09,899
We were fighting, a little bit, when I

6990
04:07:09,899 --> 04:07:12,360
